description:
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consultant in Older People’s Mental Health Services &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Post &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an outstanding consultant psychiatrist to join our Older Peoples Mental Health Service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As a consultant in the community service, you will be responsible for providing high quality care to community patients via outpatient clinics, based at Mount Gould Local Care Centre. As a senior clinician you will be at the core of decision making in patient care and service provision working closely with both medical and operational management. You will be forward thinking and able to provide sound clinical leadership to the experienced multi-disciplinary team with ease.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Along with the community aspect, this role also provides a unique opportunity to input into other areas within the service. For instance, we have an excellent ECT Service for the adult and elderly population, which you will have the opportunity to input to. There is also the opportunity to provide guidance and support to a number of trainees that rotate through the department and across the directorate. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Employing only 25 senior psychiatrists, LSW has a unique ability to provide doctors with job plans that are exclusively tailored to suit. Opportunities to be involved in research, appraisals, and audit are just a few. You will take an active awareness in LSW management, sharing advice and contributing to senior meetings as appropriate. With a robust Clinical Leadership Management structure, doctors are supported and encouraged to apply for roles to enhance their growth, be it as an Education or Clinical Supervisor or a member of the Medical Management Team. LSW believe in their doctors and their ability to contribute to the development of the organisation as a whole. We also fully support our doctors to stay connected to what interests them, even outside of their field of specialty, to ensure a career that stays exciting and engaged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Here at Livewell Southwest, we like to do things differently. As one of the UK’s only providers of physical, mental and social healthcare services for people of all ages and one of the UKs largest health and social care Community Interest Companies, we are able to offer medical jobs which are unique and tailored to you. Doctors are provided with a generous study leave allowance of 33 days over three years. We also encourage participation in the Out of Hours on Call Rota (currently 1 in 14) with appropriate compensatory rest provision. Inclusion in the teaching of trainee doctors is expected and you will receive access to our weekly teaching programme and regular peer group and reflective practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;LSW is rated good and outstanding in areas by the CQC and our staff are committed to improve on ratings year on year. We know our staff are our biggest asset and so we strive to make careers that are personal, unique and flexible. We are extremely proud partners of both Plymouth University and Plymouth University Peninsula School of Medicine and Dentistry (PUPSMD) and have received exceptional feedback in our GMC survey from the trainees that have been on rotation with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, what are you waiting for? We have a strong reputation as being an employer of choice and often have trainees and previous recruits returning to us, why not come and join us and see what we are made of!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about this exciting opportunity, please contact; Dr Dev Joardar, Clinical Lead for Older Peoples Mental Health at djoardar@nhs.net or Dr Soni Bhate, Clinical Director for Mental Health at vaishali.bhate@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The necessary information;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full GMC Registration with a licence to practice is required, as is entry on the Specialist register.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS pension is available for those who are eligible. Pension through other providers is available should the former not apply to you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Those pursuing CESR are also encouraged to apply, to be considered for a “locum to substantive” transitional position. Our department has a track record of supporting doctors through the CESR process and would welcome the opportunity to support you through it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The interview date is to be confirmed but likely to take place in early December 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
